    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Washington</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 1. 1863</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p>I feel bound to you as an old friend and<lb/> associate in the garden of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> to <sic>anounce</sic><lb/> to you the decease of
                my father-in-law <persName>Rabbi<lb/> P. M. Heilprin</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hereby I enclose a Necrologue,<lb/> which I wish you may insert in
                your next<lb/> No of the Occident in the language as<lb/> I composed it and <hi
                    rend="underline">verbally—</hi>provided it<lb/> would <sic>corrospond</sic> with
                your intention.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The memory of the that great man deserves<lb/> it, that
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> should know, who he<lb/> was—as a century may pass
                    <sic>untill</sic><lb/> another <persName>Heilprin</persName> will be born.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you find it more proper, please<lb/> translate it in English—as I
                have but<lb/> little capacity for it—and I request<lb/> you to send me two copies of
                that<lb/> No by mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should you decline it altogether—<lb/> please return me the
                writing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In every way I remain with<lb/> high regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">M. I. Franklin</persName>
            </p>
